@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "ezaMaze" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0.

                             How to play?

  Your position is indicated by a smiling face icon at the center
of the display. To play, click on a space in the general direction
you want to move. If the move is possible (no walls blocking in the
choosen direction), the display is then updated at the new position.
Note that you can also use the cursor keys to move in the maze.

  The exit tile is marked by an "E" (or "Exit") and is always
located in a dead end. When you get there, the game ends and
displays how many moves it took to get there, then ezaMaze creates
a new maze to explore...

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

LABYRINTH SIZE
--------------

  To change the labyrinth size, click on the "Game size" button.
This will clear the main window and display a large area with a
black rectangle. Click in the area and a new black rectangle will
appear with its lower right edge at the position you clicked on. At
the upper right in the window, a "Board size" text displays the
area of that black rectangle which is the size of the labyrinth.
Note that you can also use the cursor keys to change the labyrinth
size.

  When you have choosen a labyrinth size you like, click on the
"use" button and the game will return to 'play mode' where you will
be able to play with a labyrinth of that size.

  However, if you want to keep the initial labyrinth size either
click on the "cancel" button or the window's closebutton (or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key) and the game will return to the
displayed labyrinth.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game, when in the 'main game mode', by clicking
on the game window's close button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

